President Obama has nominated Gayle E. Smith as the Administrator of the U.S. Agency for International Development (USAID). Susan E. Rice, the National Security Advisor, expressed her pleasure with the nomination, highlighting Gayle's field experience, leadership skills, intellect, and knowledge of international development. Gayle has served at high levels of government for nearly 15 years and has been instrumental in promoting food security, global health, Power Africa, and the Ebola response. If confirmed by the Senate, Gayle will lead USAID during a crucial time for international development and humanitarian response.